  "shortDescription": "Browser-based eye-tracking via WebAssembly, no install needed.",
  "description": "A browser-based eye-tracking library implemented using WebAssembly technology. Peekr enables web-based eye-tracking experiments that can run directly in modern browsers without additional software installation. Full documentation and implementation details are available on the GitHub repository. This tool facilitates online eye-tracking research for event cognition and visual attention studies.",
